{
  "id": "phekb-hypertension-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "hypertension",
  "name": "Hypertension - Comprehensive Provider Query",
  "description": "Simulates a primary care provider identifying their complete hypertension-treated population. The PheKB resistant-HTN algorithm requires both HTN diagnosis OR elevated BP measurements PLUS antihypertensive medication. Real-world identification primarily unions: HTN diagnosis codes, antihypertensive prescriptions, and elevated BP measurements. With antihypertensive cross-indication and silent hypertension common, the union catches different documentation patterns.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete hypertension-treated patient population for a quality initiative on BP control. From clinical experience, HTN patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal diagnosis code (essential, benign, malignant, systolic, or labile HTN), most are on at least one antihypertensive class, and many have measured SBP > 140 mmHg on at least one office visit.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any hypertension diagnosis (essential, benign, malignant, systolic, or labile)\n2. Patients prescribed antihypertensive medications (ACE-I, ARB, CCB, BB, or diuretic)\n3. Patients with systolic blood pressure measurements above 140 mmHg\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found across these three approaches.",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of HTN dx codes, antihypertensive Rx, and elevated SBP observations. Tests provider-level identification combining diagnosis, medication, and vital-signs evidence streams.",
    "expected_queries": [
      "Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|59621000,http://snomed.info/sct|1201005,http://snomed.info/sct|78975002,http://snomed.info/sct|429457004,http://snomed.info/sct|371125006",
      "MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|29046,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|52175,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|17767,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|20352,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|4603",
      "Observation?code=http://loinc.org|8480-6&value-quantity=gt140"
    ],
